{"books":{"28":{"id":"8466","title":"Your Word is your Wand","description":"Long before affirmations entered the mainstream, Florence Scovel Shinn (1871-1940), an American book illustrator, was writing about them in her short, pithy metaphysical books. Following the success of her self-published 'The Game of Life & How to Play it' (1925) (also available on Librivox), she became a much-sought-after spiritual leader in the New Thought circles. 'Your Word is your Wand' is her second book, which impresses upon the reader the creative power of the spoken word and contains, like her first book, many potent affirmations and \"treatments\" for attracting love, wealth and positive solutions to the varied vicissitudes of daily life. Modern writers, including the influential Louise Hay, acknowledge her as an early influence.  - Summary by Spiritualbeing","url_text_source":"http:\/\/www.sacred-texts.com\/nth\/shinn\/wyw\/index.htm","language":"English","copyright_year":"1928","num_sections":"29","url_rss":"http:\/\/librivox.org\/rss\/8466","url_zip_file":"","url_project":"","url_librivox":"","url_other":null,"totaltime":"","totaltimesecs":0,"authors":[{"id":"5299","first_name":" Florence Scovel","last_name":"Shinn","dob":"1871","dod":"1940"}],"url_iarchive":"","sections":[{"id":"300735","section_number":"1","title":"Your Word is Your Wand","listen_url":"https:\/\/librivox.org\/uploads\/smijen\/yourwordisyourwand_1_shinn_128kb.mp3","language":"English","playtime":"0","file_name":null,"readers":[{"reader_id":"1630","display_name":"spiritualbeing"}]},{"id":"300736","section_number":"2","title":"Success","listen_url":null,"language":"English","playtime":"0","file_name":null,"readers":[{"reader_id":"1630","display_name":"spiritualbeing"}]},{"id":"300737","section_number":"3","title":"Prosperity","listen_url":null,"language":"English","playtime":"0","file_name":null,"readers":[{"reader_id":"1630","display_name":"spiritualbeing"}]},{"id":"300738","section_number":"4","title":"Happines